figure 4b & Sfigure5

Heatmaps showing how T1D GWAS loci influence immune phenotypes

Similar as figure 4a, we got reported T1D GWAS SNPs p values from immnue phenotype QTL mapping. While, figure 4a is trying to get the general impacts from all T1D GWAS loci on general immune phenotype categories, but in these figures, we want to show the effect from each GWAS SNP on each immune cell type or cytokine stimulation pair.

*We performed a permutation anlysis previously to evaluate the significance of GWAS loci effects compared to a 1000 random selected independent loci (See methods). Those results were also shown in the figures.

library(pheatmap)

Immune cell proportion traits.

dat<-read.table("/Users/xiaojing/Documents/working/projects/300DM/GWAS_in_DM/matrix_cc.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,check.names = F)

name<-read.table("~/Documents/working/database/300DM/cc_mapping/anno.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,sep="\t",check.names = F)

cc<-rownames(name)

matrix_cc<-dat[,cc]

names(matrix_cc)<-name$name

load("~/Documents/working/database/300DM/raw_data/preprocess/cc_all_colors.Rdata")

#####results from permutation
anno<-transform(anno,significance=rep(0,nrow(anno)))
anno$significance[c(45,53,67,75,68,69,34,38,5,6)]<-1
anno$significance<-as.factor(anno$significance)

annotation_colors$significance<-c("0"="white","1"="#808069")
#####

col=colorRampPalette(c("blue","white", "tomato")) (16)
anno<-anno[,-3]

SNP_order<-read.table("/Users/xiaojing/Documents/working/projects/300DM/GWAS_in_DM/T1D_GWAS_list_anno.txt",row.names = 1)
SNP_order<-SNP_order[rownames(matrix_cc),]

order<-order(SNP_order$V4)
SNP_order<-SNP_order[order,]
order<-order(SNP_order$V3)
SNP_order<-SNP_order[order,]

matrix_cc<-matrix_cc[rownames(SNP_order),]

matrix_cc<-t(matrix_cc)

pheatmap(matrix_cc,cluster_cols = F,annotation_row = anno,annotation_colors = annotation_colors,col=col,breaks = seq(-8,8,1),legend_breaks = seq(-8,8,2),fontsize = 10,width = 10)

dat<-read.table("/Users/xiaojing/Documents/working/projects/300DM/GWAS_in_DM/matrix_cyto.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,check.names = F)

anno<-read.table("~/Documents/working/database/300DM/phenotype_correlation/cytokine/anno.txt",header=T,row.names = 1,sep="\t")

anno<-anno[,-c(1,3)]

###fix the capital error
rownames(anno)[104]<-"BorreliaMix_PBMC_7d_IFNy"
###

library(RColorBrewer)
library(pheatmap)

mycol_Stimulations=brewer.pal(7, c("Set2"))
mycol_Cytokine=c(brewer.pal(9,"Pastel1"),"aquamarine")
mycol_Time=c("pink","lightblue")

names(mycol_Cytokine)<-as.character(unique(anno$Cytokine))
names(mycol_Stimulations)<-as.character(unique(anno$Stimus_Type))
names(mycol_Time)<-as.character(unique(anno$Time))

annotation_colors<-list(Stimus_Type=mycol_Stimulations,Cytokine=mycol_Cytokine,Time=mycol_Time)

#####results from permutation
anno<-transform(anno,significance=rep(0,nrow(anno)))
anno$significance[c(3,4,6,108,8,12,15,16,21,29,49,50,54,56,57,77,92,96,99)]<-1
anno$significance<-as.factor(anno$significance)
annotation_colors$significance<-c("0"="white","1"="#808069")

#####
col=colorRampPalette(c("blue","white", "tomato")) (16)

SNP_order<-read.table("/Users/xiaojing/Documents/working/projects/300DM/GWAS_in_DM/T1D_GWAS_list_anno.txt",row.names = 1)
SNP_order<-SNP_order[rownames(dat),]

order<-order(SNP_order$V4)
SNP_order<-SNP_order[order,]
order<-order(SNP_order$V3)
SNP_order<-SNP_order[order,]

dat<-dat[rownames(SNP_order),]
dat<-t(dat)

pheatmap(dat,cluster_cols = F,annotation_row = anno,annotation_colors = annotation_colors,col=col,breaks = seq(-8,8,1),legend_breaks = seq(-8,8,2),fontsize = 10,width = 10,border_color = F)
